laboratory_examinations.findings: Dependent atelectasis. No consolidation, and no pleural or pericardial effusion. Liver is normal in size and attenuation with a single hypodense lesion measuring 7 mm at the dome, segment VII, too small to characterize. Normal gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands. An 11-mm cyst in the lower pole of the left kidney and smaller nonspecific punctate hypodensities in the right kidney. Abnormal appendix measuring up to 11 mm, fluid-filled, with a hyperdense appendicolith at the base. Mild periappendiceal fat stranding noted. No free fluid or free air to suggest perforation.
HOLD. SPECIMEN TO BE HELD 48 HOURS AND DISCARDED.
